<div id="option_continue" style="display:none">
    His eyes narrowed — not with rage, but pain. The kind that cracked under the weight of a thousand wrong choices.
    <br /><br />
    <<dom>>
        You’ve changed.
    <</dom>>
    <br />
    <<dom>>
        You smell different. Like a man who’s already made up his mind.
    <</dom>>
    <br />
    You turned to leave. But before the door fully closed behind you, he called out.
    <br /><br />
    <<dom>>
        Come to dinner after few days. Just the three of us. One last proper meal.
    <</dom>>
    <br />
    You didn't answer. But you stood there in the hallway for several long seconds before walking away.
    Your heart beat like a war drum.
